benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{accountEmailId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account email audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request - Successful retrieval with valid accountId/accountEmailId (TC01).
Empty Response - 200 with empty array when no audit logs exist (TC02).
Query Parameters - Handling of extra parameters and validation of IDs (TC10, TC05, TC06).
Authorization - Tests for missing and invalid authentication (TC07, TC08).
Not Found / Bad Request - 404 for non-existent accounts or emails (TC03, TC04, TC18, TC19).
400 Bad Request - Invalid accountId/accountEmailId formats (TC05, TC06, TC13, TC14).
Ordering/Schema - Order by changeDate (TC15); schema validation (TC16).
Security/Validation - SQL injection and XSS scenarios (TC13, TC14).
gaps: Pagination: No tests for API-level pagination (e.g., page/size parameters, cursors).
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate-limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Forbidden access (403): No tests for authenticated users with insufficient privileges.
End-to-end performance under load: no explicit multi-user concurrency tests.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests (page/size, page tokens) and verify boundaries.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure stability under high request rate.
Add caching headers validations (ETag, Cache-Control) and caching behavior tests.
Add 403 Forbidden case to cover insufficient privileges.
Include end-to-end performance tests under load and concurrency scenarios.
Clarify or align test data to reduce reliance on hard-coded IDs and ensure consistent test data.
